Not sure if this is related (ie. should be in this PR or a followup), but this still fails AFAIK:

```
fun Foo(children: () -> Unit) {}
fun Bar(children: () -> Unit) {
    Foo {
        val c = true
        if (c) {
            throw RuntimeException()
        } else {
            children()
        }
    }
}
```

@madsager  your approach is one of possible solution.
But maybe best to move COERCION_TO_UNIT inside branches
But I'm not sure would it be much more tricky.
It's also intresting to mix long and int types in branches, e.g.:
```
fun test(arg: Int) {
    if (arg == 1) {
        result = "firstResult"
        longValue
    } else if (arg == 2) {
        result = "secondResult"
        arg
    }
}
```
